K8S effective Command:
kubectl get events
kubectl delete deployments <Deployment_Name>
kubeclt delete service <Service_Name>
kubectl delete pod <Pod_Name>
kubectl scale --replica <number_of_replicas> deployment/<name_of_deployment>
kubectl get rc (getting replica set)
kubectl get deployments
kubectl describe deployment <name>
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods --all-namespaces
kubectl get pods --all-namespaces -o wide (list all pods in the cluster in detail
kubectl get namespaces
kubectl describe pod 


Expose the deployments:
kubectl expose deployment ....
